<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN215">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kavaikkatir varaki ṉavaippuṟu vākka</l>
<l>ṟāteru maṟukiṟ pōtoṭu potuḷiya</l>
<l>vēḷai veṇpū veṇṭayir koḷīi</l>
<l>yāymaka ḷaṭṭa vampuḷi mitavai</l>
<l>yavarai koyyuna rāra māntun</l>
<l>teṉṉam poruppa ṉaṉṉāṭ ṭuḷḷum</l>
<l>picirō ṉeṉpave ṉuyirōm punaṉē</l>
<l>celvak kālai niṟpiṉu</l>
<l>mallaṟ kālai nillalaṉ maṉṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Even in the good land of the one from the Southern heights, (6)</l>
<l>where those who pluck field beans feed to satiation (5)</l>
<l>on the sweet-sour food that was cooked by a cowherd woman (4)</l>
<l>from a pounded preparation of fork-eared wild millet, (1)</l>
<l>imbuing white curd with the white flower of Vēḷai, (3)</l>
<l>that was full with buds from the street with pollen [and] dung, (2)</l>
<l>the one they call Picirōṉ will protect my life. (7)</l>
<l>Even though he may stay [away] at a time of affluence, (8)</l>
<l>he will not stay [away] at a time of affliction. (9)  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
